The paper deals with a data structure for range reporting, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. The focus is on color range reporting, which is a variant of the orthogonal range reporting problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational geometry techniques, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely category. The problem of color range reporting can also be seen as a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of extending the result to the external memory model, which is a topic in machine learning and data mining (cs.DL).
